Troubleshooting

Missing LLM configuration:
  Symptom:
    Source digest runs fail before processing starts.
  Check:
    `llm.provider` and `llm.model` in config or the matching env vars.

Unexpected format errors:
  Symptom:
    The CLI rejects an input or output format.
  Check:
    The file extension, or pass `--input-format` / `--output-format` explicitly.

stdin or stdout misuse:
  Symptom:
    The CLI rejects interactive stdin or `--verbose` with stdout output.
  Check:
    Pipe text into stdin, or write digest output to a file when using `--verbose`.

sdpub command failure:
  Symptom:
    `sdpub` subcommands reject flags or input.
  Check:
    `sdpub` requires `--input <path>` to an existing archive file.
    `cat` also requires `--serial <id>`.

Binary cover output blocked:
  Symptom:
    `sdpub cover` refuses to write to the terminal.
  Check:
    Redirect stdout or pipe the bytes elsewhere.

